Russia Allows Poultry Imports From Pilgrim’s, Sanderson Plants

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-03-28T16:42:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/russia-allows-poultry-imports-from-pilgrim-s-sanderson-plants.html
Russia allowed poultry imports from
a  Pilgrim’s Pride Corp. (PPC)  plant in Douglas, Georgia, and a
 Sanderson Farms Inc. (SAFM)  plant in Collins, Mississippi, as of March
23, the  U.S. Department of Agriculture  said.  Russia also will allow shipments from House Of Raeford
Farms Inc. in Raeford,  North Carolina ; Claxton Poultry Farms in
Claxton, Georgia; Wayne Farms in Jack, Alabama; VersaCold
Logistics Services in Mobile, Alabama; and Millard Refrigerated
Services in Statesville, North Carolina, the USDA’s Food Safety
and Inspection Service said in a  report  on its website dated
March 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
